.:: Puzzle 6x4-Level-2-18::.
There 4 different types of food: artichoke, peach, pear, radish
4 different games are played: whist, billiard, canasta, snooker
The people have 4 different jobs:  bartender, fisherman, social-worker, writer
House: modern, townhouse, gothic-revival, colonial
There are 4 different nationalities: australian, british, italian, turkish
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, snowmobile, train, trike
 1. the person eating artichoke is on the right of the social-worker##1
 2. the gothic-revival house is between the writer and the bartender##2
 3. the person eating pear is on the right of the person eating radish##1
 4. the colonial house is on the right of the fisherman##1
 5. the person driving the car is on the right of the australian##1
 6. the person playing billiard is between the person driving the car and the british##2
 7. the person driving the trike is between the australian and the person driving the snowmobile##2
 8. the person driving the car is on the right of the person eating peach##1
 9. the person playing canasta is on the right of the townhouse house##1
10. the person playing canasta is the writer##1
11. the fisherman is on the left of the british##1
12. the person playing whist is on the left of the person driving the trike##1
13. the italian is the person eating artichoke##1
14. the person playing billiard is the person playing billiard##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2      |       3       |      4      |
| Food          | radish     | pear        | peach         | artichoke   |
| Game         | whist     | canasta     | billiard    | snooker |
| Job           | fisherman  | writer      | social-worker | bartender   |
| House   | townhouse   | colonial | gothic-revival        | modern       |
| Nationality   | turkish    | british     | australian    | italian     |
| Transport     | snowmobile | trike       | train         | car         |

